Boil a full #kettle{}.

Trim the @green beans{80%grams}, then cut into thirds.

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @British pork mince{240%grams} and green beans, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @egg noodle nest{125%grams}, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain and run with cold water.

Meanwhile, open the remaining sachets.

Once browned, add the @coleslaw mix{120%grams} to the pork. Stir-fry, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @gochujang paste{30%grams}, @ketjap manis{50%grams}, @soy sauce{25%ml} and a splash of water. Bring to the boil and simmer, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the cooked noodles and toss to coat.

Share the noodles between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!